@quotation
The acts of the mind, wherein it exerts its power over simple ideas, are
chiefly these three: @w{1. Combining} several simple ideas into one compound one,
and thus all complex ideas are made.  @w{2. The second} is bringing two ideas,
whether simple or complex, together, and setting them by one another so as to
