       -: 45              b: 98
       *: 42
@end example

@noindent
which has two subtables.  (The subtables don't need a special header symbol,
since the key that identifies the subtable serves this purpose.)

@float
@anchor{Figure 3.23}
@ifinfo
@strong{Figure 3.23:} A two-dimensional table.

@example
